 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uskystormthunderbolt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SkystormThunderbolt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/5/01 2:34:48 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 43+ quad spots for light races ?</span><hr size=1> At 43 you can quad Yeti's in dreadlands - not at 44 though. They will be green.<br>
<br>
Quick exp from 40-43. Not sure after that - I am yet to find out.<br>
<br>
Skystorm Thunderbolt<br>
43rd Wizard - Tholuxe Paells <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukyriaadariath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kyria Adariath</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/5/01 6:03:21 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 43+ quad spots for light races ?</span><hr size=1> solo through 45 at spiders in Nurga. Solo you're still getting exp for pretty much all green briars as well as the obvious blue ones, and it's just ridiculously awesome exp. Once you hit 46, you get to tough it out somewhere (I solo'ed in DL outside KC when I couldn't group inside) until you get 51, then it's easy quad'ing in BW on hornets and other stuff.<br>
<br>
Ky<br>
Evoker of Tunare<br>
Knights of Vallon, Leader  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uknolanncaelestis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Knolann Caelestis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/5/01 6:21:28 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 43+ quad spots for light races ?</span><hr size=1> Quad kite Bloodgill Goblins in LoIO. Only downside might be someone is already doing them. People who can't figure out how to pull mobs from the lake need not apply. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www,kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/5/01 7:12:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 43+ quad spots for light races ?</span><hr size=1> Too bad the Eye of Zomm doesn't swim better. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umaultar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maultar</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/6/01 5:48:09 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Dumb Question</span><hr size=1> Why is OT not an option in PVP? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uronos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ronos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/6/01 6:08:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 43+ quad spots for light races ?</span><hr size=1> Maultar  <br>
Why is OT not an option in PVP?  <br>
Not really a dumb question though.<br>
If he is on Tallon or Vallon Zek its a race war and we would kill any light that would dare set foot in our lands. I get the same treatment when I port over to Greater Fey or Dreadlands, wizards blasting me to peices.<br>
We live by a few extra advantages adn disadvantages there.<br>
<br>
<br>
Ronos <p>"There are not fifty ways of fighting, there is only one: to be the conqueror."
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=haksel>Haksel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/6/01 6:12:15 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 43+ quad spots for light races ?</span><hr size=1> By the way, i'm about to hit level 34, and i hope to make my first attempt at quad kiting this weekend. I'm currently in FM. <br>
I'd like to ask to wise high level wizards (yeah, that's you) where i could go to do so...<br>
I was planning on going to Ill Omen, getting a sow and practicing a bit at the Sarnak's fort. any better suggestions ? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umaultar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maultar</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/6/01 6:29:23 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 43+ quad spots for light races ?</span><hr size=1> I quit quad kiting at 34 in omen.  I havn't really started since.  AOE's really suck after that it starts to not kill fast enuf.  That is one thing that they should address I think.  You guys all like to bitch about these high uber level things but damn..... AOE's for lev 34-51 suck. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uheihache.showPublicProfile?language=EN>heihache</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/6/01 6:30:25 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 43+ quad spots for light races ?</span><hr size=1> I would recommend practicing it on greens (as you are) but instead of the sarnaks, try the Gobbie tunnels.  Easier to get 4 out of there than out of the Sarnak fort, the fort is Heavily camped (or it is on my server, Veeshan).  Practice there.  Once you thing you got it, I'd say head down to Iceclad.  Before you go, make sure you have levitate and SOW on as the port spot is VERY VERY dangerous for a lvl 34.  Once ported in, run straight out till you hit the shoreline.  Turn to the right (shore on left) and run that way.  Go till you see a bunch of little ice bergs going off to the next island.  Follow these till you come to the gnoll camp, con them first, my first time there, I was indifferent, not sure if that is true to all races. You should see a big Tower infront of you. Turn to the right (water on right) and move up a bit away from camp.  You'll have to tinker, but usually up and down the shore line there is safe to kite, now just go out and find yourself some Snow Cougars and kite them on the shore.  Loot sucks really, other than Cougar Claw earings.  O, one thing, stay clear of Midnight (named Cougar that is black)..... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=haksel>Haksel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/6/01 6:36:14 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 43+ quad spots for light races ?</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the advice. <br>
regarding Iceclad, my last try in Velious left me quite reluctant to go back ther : 1 hour to prepare a CC guild &quot;raid&quot;, 2 minutes to die, 3 hours to get the corpses back (and a rez, hopefully !)<br>
As for post 34 AoE, it's weird, because i've always heard and read that it was the exact opposite : it's only post 34 (with spells like CoF) that a wizard can start quad kiting.<br>
I might be wrong though.<br>
My other concern is that i've only got 160 int, so i might run of mana quite quickly. (but i don't have the pp to increase it right now)<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=haksel>Haksel</A> at: 4/6/01 6:37:48 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umaultar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maultar</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/6/01 11:22:27 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 43+ quad spots for light races ?</span><hr size=1> A lot of ppl do.. I just think 216 dd sucks bigtime. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www,kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/6/01 11:39:14 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 43+ quad spots for light races ?</span><hr size=1> That's a little known secret about quad kiting: Wizards run out of mana doing it, you need a really well-equipped, high INT and mana caster to try to make it work until the 50s, possibly beyond then. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umaultar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maultar</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/6/01 12:54:51 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 43+ quad spots for light races ?</span><hr size=1> I have 198 int had 200.  Also 1900 some odd mana.  Never ran out of mana but was hoping I could squeeze 2 rounds of quadding with one bar of mana.  Imagine quadding at 50 hittin blues for 216.  ridiculous. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www,kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/6/01 2:29:53 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 43+ quad spots for light races ?</span><hr size=1> That's kind of the problem I tried to get Verant to see in the Class Talks... the AE spells are too weakly distributed (we actually get more Al'Krapor spells below level 50 than both pillar and pbae) to really use well.  Level 34 is great... but its a long ways to level 50 from there, and you can't use Supernova. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uxalos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xalos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/26/01 1:16:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 43+ quad spots for light races ?</span><hr size=1> Kyria : In Nurga. Did you stick to the pairs of sipders or did you take the larger room with the 4 spawn or all of it. Nurja's the best group xp 35-40. never thought about trying to solo there but there is enough room with the wide halls.<br>
<br>
 <p><A HREF="http://interealms.com/profiles/profile.cfm?ID=7174">Xalos</A><BR>
Pathfinder of Karana<BR>
Karana</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uyisten.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yisten</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/16/01 10:01:20 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 43+ quad spots for light races ?</span><hr size=1> I've been quading Ulthork Hunters/warriors in EW for about 5 levels now.. 35-40. I have 203INT and a couple  mana items and hardly ever run oom with them. I'm still getting pretty decent exp from them at 40 now and will prolly stay for another lvl or so.<br>
Also, hitting 4 mobs at once for 218 damage suits me just fine with these Ulthorks. I am somewhat disappointed we don't get an upgrade for so long. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/18/01 8:47:21 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 43+ quad spots for light races ?</span><hr size=1> You heard right, EW for the thorks. I am about to hit 44 and I still get exp from all thorks, even the green ones. Most nights this area is not over camped, and when it is, you can just kite giants until some people leave. Good exp and an easy kite. Lots of open space and lots of thorks to go around. If you get too many rhinos and bunnies around - whack some of them, they are all on the same spawn table. Do not try to multi kite rhinos at this level. Unless you have uber equipment with lots of extra mana you will go oom before they are dead. <p><span style="font-size: 18px; font-famliy: arial"><b>Wandor Kilbringer<br>Wizard of the 43rd Conclave<br>Vini, Vidi, Nuki</b></span><br>
<i>I came, I saw, I nuked the crap out of everything in sight!</i></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showMessage?topicID=21.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showMessage?topicID=28.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.emailToFriend?topicID=12.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.threadControl?topicID=12.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=12.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=12.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm1">General Discussion<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm3">Trade Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm4">Rant Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm8">Mob Dropped Spells<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm10">Class Balance & Class Bugs<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm22">Out of Mana<option value="graffeswizardc